      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "DEWANA STAR (1) has a fair record and proved too strong last time to win by 8 lengths at Warragul in a handy 25.44 beating No Iron Team. Comes out of a solid form race last start. Has hit winning form and can go on with it. CRACKERJACK RALF (6) had been in top form scoring three consecutive wins before a minor placing (23.24) last time at Horsham. Tends to go well on this box draw. Super consistent and can feature with the right run. PAW MATIC (7) finished second last start over 450m at this track but was game in defeat in a fast 25.10. This is tougher but looks a leading chance again. MATT LOCH (2) has merit but will need to be at his best to take this out.",
